      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "aspnet_PersonalizationAdministration_DeleteAllState",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to delete personalization state data from a SQL Server database for a specified application. It can delete either all user-specific personalization data or only the data shared among all users, depending on the input parameters. The procedure also returns the number of rows affected by the deletion operation."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Low"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure is relatively straightforward, involving basic SQL operations such as conditional logic, deletion of records, and retrieval of an application ID. It does not involve complex joins, subqueries, or advanced SQL features."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
